  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6933 sitting between the flip at 6857 and massive positive gamma wall at 6950 (+16.1B), dealers are currently long gamma and will sell into any push toward 6950 while buying the dip if we test 6900 support. The PIN regime combined with this heavy positive gamma concentration creates a strong magnet effect around current levels, with dealers acting as stabilizers against the recent -1.4% move over 5 minutes. Watch 6950 as the critical resistance where dealer selling pressure intensifies, and 6900 as the key support level where dealer buying should emerge.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6925-6940 range as dealers counteract the recent selling pressure.",
